message.content:
1. After arthroscopy, patients were randomized to receive different treatments.
2. One group of patients received five injections of HA1.
3. HA1 is also known as Suprahyal®/Adant®.
4. Another group of patients received four injections of HA2.
5. HA2 is also known as Orthovisc®.
6. Another group of patients received three injections of HA3.
7. HA3 is also known as Synvisc®.
8. Another group of patients received a single injection of PRP.
9. PRP is also known as GPSTM II.
10. Another group of patients received standard care.
11. The group that received standard care is referred to as the control group.

messages.content:
Statement: After arthroscopy, patients were randomized to receive 1) five injections of HA1 (Suprahyal®/Adant®); 2) four injections of HA2 (Orthovisc®); 3) three injections of HA3 (Synvisc®); 4) a single injection of PRP (GPSTM II); or 5) standard care (control).
